  "title": "Multiple search inputs collision",
  "body": "I have two input field that searches. First for text search, second search by zip code.\r\nI have added a custom widget for the second input field for search, and I use helper.search(); for manually search.\r\n\r\nSteps: \r\nSearch result by zipcode => Click on result => click back browser button => I found first input field filled with zip code that I searched for the second input.\r\nThat is because query=98072 going internally and when I hit back button it comes back in URL and filled automatically. Please suggest me a solution either send \"query\" and \"q\" as the parameter or stop URL filled automatically.",
